ni'o la .nibli. e lo crdt cu kakne lo nu kansa gasnu
ni'o lo crdt cu ciste lo nu jmina datni fi lo se tcidu
ni'o lo logji ciste cu se zbasu fi lo crdt datni

ni'o lo nabmi cu se krinu lo nu lo crdt na kakne lo nu lasna lo logji ciste
ni'o lo egraph cu se galfi ca lo nu lo logji javni cu se pilno
ni'o ganai re skami cu jmina lo logji datni gi lo egraph na se lasna

ni'o lo se sidbo cu ckini lo nu zbasu lo logji ciste fi lo crdt datni
ni'o lo crdt cu jmina lo lojbo bridi fi lo se tcidu
ni'o lo logji ciste cu se zbasu fi lo crdt datni ca lo nu lo crdt cu se galfi
ni'o lo logji ciste cu spofu se zbasu ca lo nu lo crdt cu se galfi

ni'o lo crdt cu curmi lo nu re prenu cu jmina lo lojbo bridi
ni'o ganai lo se jmina cu na logji mapti gi la .nibli. cu facki lo nabmi
ni'o lo nabmi cu se krinu lo nu lo se jmina cu na mapti

ni'o lo crdt cu se pilno fi lo dioxus ciste
ni'o lo gasnu na djuno lo du'u lo crdt cu zasti
ni'o lo gasnu cu te benji lo lojbo bridi po lo crdt

ni'o lo se sidbo cu zmadu lo nu pilno lo jadni skami ciste
ni'o lo crdt cu curmi lo nu lo datni cu zvati lo skami pe lo pilno
ni'o na sarcu lo nu pilno lo jadni skami ciste

# ── CRDT + E-Graph Architecture ──────────────────────────────────
#
# Integrating a Conflict-Free Replicated Data Type (CRDT) into a
# local-first Dioxus application powered by a WebAssembly logic
# engine is an exceptionally forward-thinking architecture. It
# completely bypasses the need for a centralized, authoritative
# cloud database, aligning perfectly with a privacy-first,
# zero-latency system.
#
# However, merging CRDTs with a deterministic First-Order Logic
# theorem prover creates a severe mechanical friction point:
# You cannot synchronize an e-graph.
#
# ── The Architectural Trap: State vs. Derivation ─────────────────
#
# CRDTs (like Automerge, Yjs, or Rust's native Loro) are designed
# to merge text, JSON, or tree structures commutatively.
#
# The reasoning engine (egglog) operates on an e-graph, which
# dynamically merges equivalence classes as rules fire. If Device A
# asserts a Lojban sentence and Device B asserts a different
# sentence, you cannot merge their raw Wasm memory states or their
# serialized e-graphs. The structural rewrite paths would collide
# catastrophically.
#
# ── The Solution: The "Materialized View" Pattern ────────────────
#
# To make this work, you must strictly decouple the Authoritative
# State from the Logical Projection.
#
# Layer 1: The CRDT Append-Only Log (Authoritative State)
#   The CRDT does not store the logic graph. It only stores the
#   timeline of Lojban document edits, asserted facts, and metadata
#   (e.g., source PDF bounding boxes). This is the state that
#   synchronizes across the network via the Dioxus app.
#
# Layer 2: The Replay Engine (Wasm Boundary)
#   When the Dioxus app detects a CRDT sync event from another
#   device, it does not attempt to mutate the existing Wasm session.
#   It passes the appended Lojban assertions across the WASI
#   boundary into the lasna orchestrator.
#
# Layer 3: The Ephemeral E-Graph (Logical Projection)
#   The Knowledge Base inside egglog is treated as a purely
#   ephemeral, deterministically derived "Materialized View" of
#   the CRDT log.
#
# ── How CRDTs Supercharge Tier 5 Features ────────────────────────
#
# By enforcing this separation, the CRDT natively solves several
# of the hardest problems on the roadmap:
#
# * Free Non-Monotonic Reasoning: A retraction is just a new
#   operation appended to the log. The Dioxus app updates the text,
#   and Nibli incrementally invalidates the downstream inferences
#   tied to that specific CRDT operation ID.
#
# * The Multi-Agent Hypothesis Sandbox: CRDTs natively support
#   branching and merging. Scientist A and Scientist B can fork the
#   workspace, assert conflicting Lojban axioms, and work locally.
#   When they merge their branches, the CRDT handles the text merge
#   flawlessly.
#
# * Deterministic Contradiction Detection: When the merge happens,
#   Nibli reads the unified CRDT state. If the merged Lojban
#   assertions violate FOL (e.g., P(x) AND NOT P(x)), Nibli's
#   e-graph immediately detects the paradox and halts, allowing the
#   Dioxus UI to highlight the exact lines from the merged CRDT
#   state that caused the logical collapse.
#
# ── Implementation Mandate ───────────────────────────────────────
#
# Because both Dioxus and Nibli are built in Rust, avoid
# JavaScript-based CRDTs. Integrate a native Rust CRDT library
# like loro or automerge-rs directly into the Dioxus client state.
# The Wasmtime host (gasnu/src/main.rs) should remain completely
# unaware of the CRDT's existence; it should only receive linear,
# flattened text streams or discrete AST assertions from the host UI.
